{"id": "1411589752951541843", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "type": 0, "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "author_bot": false, "content": "I have a very genuine question for anyone here who's played both in English and in another language.\nHave you noticed the weird differences in the roman numerals in the game? and is the font consistent between languages? In-game I've found I prefer the look of the numerals that are just composed of actual I's and V's, but I'm concerned that it might render in-game in a different font in another language.\n\nI feel like it should all be standardized, potentially even across all languages. Should we go with `III` or `Ⅲ`? The Unicode characters (like Ⅲ) seem to have two different presentations in my excel sheet, even within the same language (see N9 vs N15), and I can't tell why. Is it like that in-game at all?", "timestamp": "2025-08-31T05:53:43.173000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1411589752637096038", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 126517, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1402941858606219294/1411589752637096038/image.png?ex=6a323667&is=6a30e4e7&hm=9343b9f53cf2038d432649c617320e795dfa5b94bd798a1f8d2139702b449418&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
